

<div class="oucontent-caption oucontent-nonumber"><span class="oucontent-figure-caption">Introducing Trevor and Dahlia</span></div></div></div><p>Then listen to the audio clips below, in which various people talk about basic needs. As you listen, note down some key words summarising these needs (for example, food, housing or work). If necessary, pause the audio player. Pay attention to needs that are most common and those mentioned only by one or two people. If you find any of the dialogues difficult to hear, you can read the transcript by using the link below the audio. You can switch on the subtitles for the video excerpts if you are using the DVD provided.</p><div class="oucontent-figure oucontent-media-mini"><img src="http://learn3.open.ac.uk/pluginfile.php/808/mod_oucontent/oucontent/103/k217_audio_trev_dhalia.png" alt="" width="200" height="149"/></div><div class="oucontent-media" style="width:342px;"><div class="oucontent-default-filter"><span class="oumediafilter"><a href="http://learn3.open.ac.uk/pluginfile.php/808/mod_oucontent/oucontent/103/k217_2010j_b1_a001_asset1.mp3?forcedownload=1" class="oumedialinknoscript">Download this audio clip.</a><span id="filter_mp3_1912422231"></span></span><script type="text/javascript">
